725990f-a.text:
174th Street, east side, north of 76th Ave., showing two homes. The brown Souse faces Fresh Meadow Road. According to Eugene L. Armbruster who received his information from Cornelius Lawrence, two owners (or occupants) were:one Hoagland; J. West, 1860; and 3. West, 1873-1891. This place seen in the two views was
demolished in May 1934.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
